title: Allegiant trailer video reveals first look at new Divergent Series movie
text:
Video Image The Divergent Series: Allegiant 1:42 Beatrice Prior and Tobias Eaton venture into the world outside of the fence and are taken into protective custody by a mysterious agency known as the Bureau of Genetic Welfare.
September 16th 2015 a month ago /video/video.news.com.au/Entertainment/ Four (Theo James) and Tris (Shailene Woodley) in a scene from The Divergent series: Insurgent.
Alison Stephenson news.com.au FANS of the Divergent series have today been treated to the first look at Allegiant, the latest film in the series.
With the tagline “Break the boundaries of your world,” Allegiant is the second last film in the franchise, with Ascendant to follow in March 2017.
Shailene Woodley, Theo James, Zoe Kravitz, Miles Teller, Naomi Watts, Octavia Spencer and Ansel Elgort will all return as will fellow Aussie Keiynan Lonsdale.
Jeff Daniels and Bill Skarsgard will join the cast.
Allegiant sees Beatrice Prior (Tris) and Tobias Eaton (Four) venture into the world outside of the fence and are taken into protective custody by a mysterious agency known as the Bureau of Genetic Welfare.
The film will be released in Australia on March 17, 2016.
